Frequently Asked Questions about Penetration Agent for Mercerization Market
What is mercerization?
Mercerization is a process in which textiles, particularly cotton, are treated with a caustic solution to increase their luster and affinity for dyes.

What is a penetration agent for mercerization?
A penetration agent is a chemical compound used in the mercerization process to enhance the penetration of the caustic solution into the textile fibers.

